        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 1:45AM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 145 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles west of Mud Butte, or 45 miles west of Faith, moving east at 35
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mud Butte, Opal, and Maurine.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
